world of small countries (like Ukraine) be divvied up among the big players=
, Yalta-style ( https://puck.news/yalta-2023-planning-for-life-after-the-ru=
ssian-invasion/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%28=
2%2F24%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%=
2F24%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3D=
f6c60617da42abd12a ). He is also, as listeners of the
About a Boy podcast ( https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/about-a-boy-the=
-story-of-vladimir-putin/id1709963682?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brigh=
test+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F24%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brighte=
st+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F24%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dc=
ustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) will remember, someone who sees =
the world as a zero-sum game: If his negotiating partner is winning, that m=
eans he=E2=80=99s losing.

=C2=A0

Moreover, he clearly doesn=E2=80=99t have much respect for Trump. (Fiona Hi=
ll, Trump=E2=80=99s
former Russia hand, recalled ( https://puck.news/fiona-hill-explains-his-pu=
tin-complex/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2=
F24%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F2=
4%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c=
60617da42abd12a ) that Putin purposely brought young, attractive interprete=
rs to his meetings with the president in order to distract him.) Putin like=
s Trump insofar as he can extract concessions and use him to destroy NATO, =
the G7, and other clubs to which the Russian leader is no longer invited. B=
ut while Trump clearly sees Putin as a natural ally, Putin doesn=E2=80=99t
return the favor. Because Putin doesn=E2=80=99t have allies. He has people =
he can use.

=C2=A0

What happens when Putin and Trump inevitably disagree on something=E2=80=94=
say, the arctic territory in which they=E2=80=99ve both shown such interest=
? Or Trump doesn=E2=80=99t bend far enough, or reaches the end of his usefu=
lness? Or when Putin violates whatever deal Trump hammers out on Ukraine? =
=E2=80=9CAt some point, American ambitions will collide with
Russian realities,=E2=80=9D one Republican foreign policy insider told me, =
=E2=80=9Cwhich is to say, the same story we have watched about a half-dozen=
 times before.=E2=80=9D

=C2=A0

The reality is that Putin has much bigger ambitions than just keeping Ukrai=
ne out of NATO or holding on to some territory. He wants to eliminate Ukrai=
ne as a real and sovereign state, and he hasn=E2=80=99t changed his goals t=
here or anywhere else. America, meanwhile, has changed
administrations and continues to do what it always does. The new guy comes =
in thinking he can succeed where all his predecessors have failed, en route=
 to crashing against the exact same rocks: Putin=E2=80=99s desire to domina=
te.

