6a9d86bb18841b1ad7f17c632" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000=
;">accused</a> her of trying to overthrow him in 2011.)=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;"><strong>Joe Biden</strong>, having served as Obama=E2=80=99s vice =
president, was the first president to come into office with a clear-eyed vi=
ew of Putin and the paltry prospects of d=C3=A9tente. In the
brief window before a series of foreign policy shitstorms consumed Biden=E2=
=80=99s presidency, his strategy for dealing with Russia was to simply keep=
 the issue at bay. And yet, as we now know, even Biden got burned. Putin, a=
s Georgetown professor <strong>Angela Stent</strong> once said, refused to =
be parked.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>Trump has so far avoided his pred=
ecessors=E2=80=99 fate. Though Moscow was disappointed in what they receive=
d during Trump=E2=80=99s first term=E2=80=94more sanctions on Russia, letha=
l aid for
